node.text: 😂😂😂 great almost true👍🤪🤣
I’m happy to report.. I found the on button ☺️
@nick.thake.photo.video that’s the Essex accent 💁🏼‍♀️
@naturewithgeorgia haha I know I’m from Gt Dunmow…. 😂
@nick.thake.photo.video are you really, you defo know then 😂
Fertys 😂
@bonnerblack 🫶🏼🦆
@ozlouise awww you have pigeon pals 🥹
Hahahha this is amazing 👏😍 I love pigeons. I have 2 that sit on the lamppost outside my window that I say hi to.
@alex_roamwild glad it made you chuckle ☺️
Love this hilarious reel 😂👏
@josteinrc I need this quote on a tote bag asap 🐦😂
@naturewithgeorgia 😂😂
You dont find birdwatching…birdwatching finds you! 🫵🏻😂
@nationalparktravelguides i can relate. Hiking was my thang before birds. I am still partial to it but the birdies have taken over 🦉

Ha 😂! I've done that with hiking.  You'll need magic shoes with special traction, so that when you trip you have something to blame (every hero story needs a villian). You'll pick the most scenic trails so you can stare at your feet the whole time (see villain, above). You get to study maps for hours.  And talk about hydration systems that you'll use to transfer fluids from your water bladder to, well, your water bladder 😁...
@stephen_j_c_photos thanks, glad you can relate 😂🫶🏼
😂🤣😂🤣. So true. Great vid
@modernchestnut get yourself out there and stare at some birds, woooo 👀🐦‍⬛
Great. What do I do next?
@everybeerd you reached the elite level, well done 👏🏼
Took it a step further and turned it into a career too!
@shawn_wildlife if you want to get the best shot… don’t take your camera 😂
So many time we see it when don't have our gear yet we don't see them when we have it
@wildlifelens1995 🫶🏼
❤️❤️❤️ best
@w.bloomfield_photos thanks ☺️
Amazing 😂
@terry_cleaver_photography awww love that you have been doing it since a kid 🫶🏼
God I must have been in my 30s since being a kid then as been a bird watcher for as long as I can remember and had my first binoculars as a child 😂😂. Great page by the way. 🙌
@giacomoloretiph why thank you ☺️
😂😂 Good quality video 👏
@richiesfov 🫶🏼🦉
@officialstickreviews APPROVED! omg I love your page 🪵
What about stick questing??
@theavtgallery thanks ☺️
Noice! 👌🔥
@daleblasingame I feel like I’m an expert in the back of birds at this point 😂
@naturewithgeorgia 😂😂😂
SO MANY back photos.
@dd_photo_uk glad you can relate 😂🫶🏼
Perfectly summed me up with this!! 😂😂
I mean this also seems like a valid reason to befriend the birdies 🦉
I thought I wanted to get into bird watching. Turns out I actually want to befriend the bird. Gain their trust. Protect them and let them protect me.
@ollieowenphotography I have a pop up hide too, wooo 💃🏼
Substitute the wooden box for a pop-up hide and I’m in 👏🏻🤣
@shawnsoter honestly the amount of times iv said this 😂
@naturewithgeorgia well, it's definitely more work when you're an ethical birder, which you clearly are.
Just turn around! Haha.
@jasonmarlowphotography I am 32 years young! Yep, totally agree. Gonna have to sell my liver to get a new lens 😂
You are in your 30’s? You forgot to add outrageously expensive cool equipment that becomes an addiction that you find yourself wanting to upgrade! 😂
@elmir_nedelchev Just how does this sound😄
@elmir_nedelchev I did eventually find the on button ☺️
Cool equipment that you "can't work out how to use"😁😆

caption.text: I’m happy to report.. I found the on button ☺️
